Description
Description
This group is for all of us Succulent Lovers who have cold wint...ers and can't plant in ground. But, we can have beautiful containers outside in summers and in winter. Let's all share our experiences with our succulents good or bad. If you ever have any problems or questions you can contact Admin. Ken Bell or Sandy Baez Crabtree.

  • Miao Chen Its not too far gone if you want to save it. Get some soapy water (1/4 mild dish soap 3/4 water) and spray the entire plant and all the other ones in the same area. Let it dry and apply for the next few days. The bugs should dry out and you can rinse the plant after. Be careful it doesnt spread!! Alternately you can us 70% alcohol to spray and keep them in a dark place entire it dries

Laura Cummings
Visual Storyteller 3 hrs

Good morning yall . Its time for coffee and succulents. Its Monday, the beginning of a new week. Its 71 outside this morning and today my spikey babies are catching my eye.. They have such beautiful structure, and they come in so many colors, shapes and sizes....most of them bite...if your not careful. And what is really cool...some of them pup like crazy..... Agave Quadricolor is one of those Agaves. Now, my Agave Ferdinand has also turned out to be ...a pup maker. The Mother plant, I have planted in ground, she had one nice size pup, and when I got her home she was very root bound and it took Wes and I to get her out...and there they were.....pups growing under the dirt....over 30 of them.....some were way to small to make it. I tried to root and save 15 of them...and 3 months later...11 of them are alive and well...still babies..but one day. They are tiny, but they are cute. I hope Momma makes it through the winter in the ground, . She is a beauty.
Yall have a marvelous Monday. Im going to try to work a couple of hours today.
He has made everything beautiful in its time.. He certainly has
